
[1]outwardly

   OUT'WARDLY, adv.

   1. Externally; opposed to inwardly; as outwardly content, but inwardly
   uneasy.

   2. In appearance; not sincerely. Many may inwardly reverence the
   goodness which they outwardly seem to despise.
